I acknowledge my flaws but never seem to find a way to really work on them so it’s not a pattern I keep doing every year. I work on them for like a month and then I’m back to where I was .. struggling.

Controlling. Overthinking. Comparing. Jealously. Self Happiness … all things I struggle with but yet mask so well. They have impacted my relationships, work life, friendships, + more

I promise you .. you are not missing out on anything (me talking to myself) O was literally itching to go to the grocery store, or anywhere JUST to say I did something. 

I love creating this type of content too because social media is always about glamorizing when in reality this is how I look half of the time. It’s not always about the aesthetics sis. 

Sometimes I don’t do laundry for days, I don’t wash dishes, I don’t make my bed, I’m in the same clothes, hair wrapped, forget to take a shower and even eat or brush my teeth .. so what. 

Take a break. Relax. You earned it ✊🏾

I’m loving myself more, dating myself more, getting to know myself all over again, and not putting an alarm clock on when my “time” is. What I’m starting to learn is when you love yourself and operate at the highest frequency, you attract people at that level. Self-love is the foundation of better connections and as women, we have to take better control, especially with our dating journeys.

As I jump back into “dating” .. lightly... I’m keeping in mind that the more self-love I have towards myself, the more open I am to new connections. I’m also normalizing open conversations around self-love, discovery, and pleasure, which is the start of creating a foundation for healthy connections.

I know Valentine’s Day is coming up and we’re going to be awkward looking at couples wondering “why not me”, or “when is it my time”, slow down and focus on your needs .. put yourself first .. set those boundaries and treat yourself as a priority so your next partner can too!

✨ LIFE LATELY. ✨ long read

I’m convinced Instagram has turned into my journal and it doesn’t matter if anyone reads these .. this is my place to vent all my thoughts.

my life lately has been a combination of some really great moments where I’m on a super high. My podcast “Dear Women, I Got Y’all” is launching soon, I’ve been landing several brand partnerships deals without any outreach, and I’ve landed a new contract. I’ve been working out consistently enough that I see results. Sounds great right?

… and there are moments where I’m questioning myself & asking, “yo wtf are you doing” or “why is this happening to me”. I’m figuring out more about myself than ever before. I truly believe a person never stops growing & no matter how old you are, you are going to run across people who bring out different sides of you & notice things about you that you don’t even see yourself.

I’ve hit this threshold in life where I’m telling myself, look you are 30 with no kids or husband, go live a stress-free life, have fun, and do whatever makes you happy or when is it my time because damn a bitch is 30. 

I’m getting to a place where .. you have to appreciate life and where you are for what it is. You can only control what’s possible everything else is faith .. god .. & life doing its thing. 

I know social media makes you think you have to be successful at a certain age or define success by designer items and luxury cars but there is a life beyond social media where every moment doesn’t have to be recorded or replayed a million times. There is a world where you can leave your phone at home when you go and be disconnected for a few hours. There is also a world where the RIGHT person will show up RIGHT ON time when you feel like you have no love or fight. 

I’m learning that...

I’m not taking my phone everywhere. I turn it off at night. I’m learning how to be disconnected .. even from my close friends because I just need that time to re-collect even though it’s uncomfortable being in my own thoughts. I’m learning that you have to forgive your past before you can allow anything amazing to enter your future. 

- signed a healing girl, figuring it TF out one day at a time. ✊🏾✊🏾

Valentine’s Day .. a day that I always want to enjoy I’m just usually solo.

But I can’t lie even though I get a little “jealous” seeing everyone else’s appreciation posts, I love seeing them. I love LOVE. I want LOVE. I want to be appreciated. I love men and women sharing the amazing things they love about their partners and what they have planned for each other. I never want to hate or compare and wonder why them and not me. Yes, I’m human just like everyone else and desire those things but I guess it’s just timing .. and I’ll take that.

This is an appreciation post for myself. I’m not perfect .. and I never want to seem to be. 4️⃣ Surround Yourself with Love: Seek support from loved ones who uplift and encourage you. Surround yourself with positive influences, people who remind you of your strength and beauty. 

5️⃣ Set Boundaries: Learn to set boundaries that honor your needs and values. Say no to things that drain your energy and yes to activities that nourish your soul. 

Look, ladies, falling back in love with yourself is a vital process, especially during challenging times. Embrace your journey with patience, compassion, and the understanding that healing takes time.
